Diffamazione (art. 595 c.p.): se l'esposto viene diffuso a terzi non competenti;
Simulazione di reato (art. 367 c.p.)

roles.ipotesiReatoEn:
Calumny (art. 368 CC): if the report contains knowingly false accusations;
Defamation (art. 595 CC): if the report is disseminated to non-competent third parties;
Simulation of crime (art. 367 CC)

roles.ipotesiReato:
Reati societari: false comunicazioni sociali (art. 2621 c.c., recl. 1-5 anni), infedeltà patrimoniale (art. 2634 c.c.), corruzione tra privati (art. 2635 c.c.);
Reati tributari: dichiarazione fraudolenta (artt. 2-3 D.Lgs. 74/2000), dichiarazione infedele (art. 4), omessa dichiarazione (art. 5), emissione di fatture false (art. 8), omesso versamento di ritenute certificate (art. 10-bis, soglia €150.000), omesso versamento IVA (art. 10-ter, soglia €250.000), indebita compensazione (art. 10-quater);
Reati fallimentari: bancarotta fraudolenta (art. 322 CCII), bancarotta semplice (art. 323 CCII), ricorso abusivo al credito (art. 325 CCII);
Reati 231: tutti i reati presupposto del D.Lgs. 231/2001 commessi nell'interesse dell'ente

roles.ipotesiReatoEn:
Corporate crimes: false corporate communications (art. 2621 CC, imprisonment 1-5 years), patrimonial infidelity (art. 2634 CC), private corruption (art. 2635 CC);
Tax crimes: fraudulent declaration (arts. 2-3 D.Lgs. 74/2000), unfaithful declaration (art. 4), omitted declaration (art. 5), issuance of false invoices (art. 8), omitted payment of certified withholdings (art. 10-bis, threshold €150,000), omitted VAT payment (art. 10-ter, threshold €250,000), improper offsetting (art. 10-quater);
Bankruptcy crimes: fraudulent bankruptcy (art. 322 CCII), simple bankruptcy (art. 323 CCII), abusive recourse to credit (art. 325 CCII);
231 offences: all predicate offences under D.Lgs. 231/2001 committed in the entity's interest

